<!--
currencies.xml
2/4/2019
written by Vicente Cartas Espinel

This file contains the different currencies used in MekHQ. Keep in mind that the currency codes are
used by the factions.xml file and by CurrencyManager.java, so if you remove or change a currency here,
you will need to do changes on those files.

Here is a description of what goes in each currency tag

name - Descriptive full name of the currency
code - Unique three-letter upper-case currency code (ISO-4217)
decimalPlaces - decimalPlaces  the number of decimal places that the currency
                normally has, from 0 to 30 (normally 0, 2 or 3)
symbol - Symbol used to represent the currency. Real currencies have their symbols
         defined by the Locale (e.g. $ or US$), but because these are fictional
         currencies we define the symbols ourselves.
defaultStart - Indicates which year the currency started being the default currency for the IS.
               Optional.
defaultEnd - Indicates which year the currency ended being the default currency for the IS.
             Mandatory if defaultStart is defined.
-->

